  26 | ///
  27 | /// A provider stream that ends (`None`) *without* first emitting a
  28 | /// [`StreamChunk::Done`] terminated prematurely: the HTTP body closed before
  29 | /// the model signalled completion. Every streaming provider emits `Done` on a
  30 | /// real finish, so a missing `Done` is a reliable "connection dropped
  31 | /// mid-turn" signal. Rather than mis-report that as [`StreamStop::Clean`]
  32 | /// (which silently accepts a truncated reply), it is classified as
  33 | /// [`StreamStop::PrematureEnd`] so the restart engine re-requests a fresh
  34 | /// stream and discards the partial.
  35 | pub(super) async fn drain(
  36 |     mut stream: BoxStream<'static, StreamChunk>,
