   1 | //! Stream Restart Protocol (SRP) engine.
   2 | //!
   3 | //! Re-opens a *fresh* provider stream when a drain pass stops for a
   4 | //! restart-eligible reason ([`StreamStop::restart_eligible`]). LLM streams are
   5 | //! not resumable mid-flight, so SRP never token-stitches a "continue": it
   6 | //! re-requests from scratch. Restarts fire when nothing usable was committed
   7 | //! (cold stall or transient fault) and also when the byte stream ended before
   8 | //! a `Done` chunk ([`StreamStop::PrematureEnd`]) — in that case any partial is
   9 | //! discarded so a complete answer replaces the truncated one. Bounded by
  10 | //! [`RestartPolicy`].
